</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[826,1441,296,715]" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">
Small to medium size species (female, 
<quantity box="[1289,1436,326,348]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.055" metricValueMax="1.15" metricValueMin="0.96" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="10.55" valueMax="11.5" valueMin="9.6">9.6–11.5 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[826,846,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">N</emphasis>
= 3; male, 
<quantity box="[1003,1118,357,378]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.45" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.9" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="8.45" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.9">7.9–9 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[1146,1166,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">N</emphasis>
= 2) with moderately broad abdomen; according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Fluke CL" box="[1229,1391,387,409]" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref46485" refString="Fluke CL. 1937. New south American Syrphidae (Diptera). American Museum Novitates 941: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1937">Fluke (1937)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fluke" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pogonosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. pogonosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KNAB" authorityYear="1913" box="[1143,1274,418,439]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvicola">
<emphasis box="[1143,1274,418,439]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. sylvicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is even more similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LANE &amp; CARRERA" authorityYear="1944" box="[1035,1189,448,470]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borgmeieri">
<emphasis box="[1035,1189,448,470]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. borgmeieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fluke" authorityYear="1937" box="[1251,1388,449,470]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pogonosa">
<emphasis box="[1251,1388,449,470]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. pogonosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basoflagellomere is oval (female, bf = 1.4–1.7), there is a ridge between the frons and the frontal prominence and the alula has an area bare of microtrichia anteriorly, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KNAB" authorityYear="1913" box="[1037,1168,571,592]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvicola">
<emphasis box="[1037,1168,571,592]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. sylvicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basoflagellomere is conspicuously elongate (bf = 2.3), there is no ridge, and the alula is wholly microtrichose. To separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fluke" authorityYear="1937" box="[826,963,663,684]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pogonosa">
<emphasis box="[826,963,663,684]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. pogonosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LANE &amp; CARRERA" authorityYear="1944" box="[1031,1184,662,684]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borgmeieri">
<emphasis box="[1031,1184,662,684]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="108">Q. borgmeieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see ‘Taxonomic notes’ under this species.
</paragraph>
